# Local overlay for van-workflow

This file is read by van-workflow on session start and appended to the engineering-discipline
system-reminder as "LOCAL OVERLAY". Use it for things that are specific to YOUR machine and
should be fresh in the agent's memory every session — but do not belong in the public plugin.

Typical sections people put here:

## Identity
Name the agent goes by on this machine. Example:

> I am Jordan's assistant on her work laptop. My scope is the web-platform team.

## Workspace
Paths, project roots, anything that helps the agent understand where things live. Example:

> - Main workspace: `~/Workspace/Acme/`
> - Active project: `payments-service`
> - Related services on the same host: `orders-api`, `users-api`

## Organization context
Which org / Jira instance / Slack workspace is in scope. Example:

> - Jira instance: `acme` (jira.acme.com)
> - Git identity: `jordan@acme.com` for all commits in this workspace

## Extra reminders
Anything that's saved you from a repeated mistake in the past. Example:

> - Never run migrations against the shared dev DB without asking — use the branch-isolated DB
> - For any API change, update the OpenAPI spec in `docs/api.yaml` and regenerate clients

## What NOT to put here
- Secrets, tokens, passwords — use your secret store instead
- Long reference material — that belongs in the project's CLAUDE.md
- Anti-patterns that apply to all developers — that's what the universal blocks are for

Short, high-salience reminders only. If a line here wouldn't make the top-5 list of things the
agent should know on every turn, it's probably too much.
